President Jacob Zuma has on Thursday appointed Lieutenant-General Lesetja Mothiba as the new Acting National Commissioner of the South African Police Service (SAPS) with immediate effect.Mothiba s appointment comes after Phahlane s acting position came to an end today.President Jacob Zuma thanked Phahlane for his sterling leadership on SAPS during his tenure. He further congratulates the new commissioner on his position. President Zuma has congratulated the new acting commissioner and wish him all the success in his new responsibility, presidency said in a statement.Phahlane has been levelled with series of allegations in the past months, ranging from corruption and defeating the ends of justice.-Sipho Jack